The paper deals with fully dynamic algorithms for maintaining certain properties of graphs, such as vertex coloring and minimum spanning forest weight approximation. This falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and graph algorithms (cs.DM). The paper also uses techniques from property testing, which is a subfield of theoretical computer science that deals with algorithms that test whether a given object satisfies a certain property. This suggests that the paper could also be classified under sub-categories such as computational geometry (cs.CG), computational complexity (cs.CC), and information theory (cs.IT), which are all related to property testing.
